      "completed_at": "2026-04-08T11:36:13.785422+00:00",
      "artifacts": {
        "changelog_entry": "[#377] Sprint D SRS preprocess chunk impl - replaces the T-SRS-002 `SRSCalibrate`, T-SRS-003 `SRSBaseline`, T-SRS-004 `SRSDenoise`, and T-SRS-005 `SRSNormalize` skeleton bodies with concrete implementations inside `packages/scieasy-blocks-srs/src/scieasy_blocks_srs/preprocess/`. `SRSCalibrate` now performs the locked digitizer inversion, rejects already-calibrated inputs, and promotes `Image` collections to typed `SRSImage` outputs; the three downstream preprocess blocks now implement the spec-locked baseline, denoise, and normalization method families while preserving typed metadata. The SRS package exports and dependency declarations are updated, the skipped preprocess test stubs are replaced with concrete behavioral coverage, and `tests/plugins/test_phase11_skeleton.py` gains `test_srs_preprocess_impl_smoke()` so the workflow gate sees top-level SRS implementation coverage. (@Codex, 2026-04-08, branch: feat/issue-377/T-SRS-002-005-srs-preprocess, session: 20260408-071425-phase-11-srs-preprocess-chunk-t-srs-002)"
